    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Breckinridge</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 12,
                                    1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 126.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 144, of the 28th
                            ultimo, reporting detention at Nieszawa, government of Warsaw, of Anton
                            Yablkowski, claiming to be an American citizen, on charges so far not
                            ascertained.</p>
                <p>I inclose copy of the application made to this Department by Anton
                            Yablkowski on which passport No. 18144 was issued. You will observe that
                            the applicant represented that he was born in Prussia.</p>
                <p>If the question of the validity of our passport should be raised, you
                            will find correspondence on the subject printed in <ref target="frus1893#pg_15">Foreign Relations, 1893, pages 15</ref> and
                                <ref target="frus1893#pg_23">23</ref>, and in <ref target="frus1894#pg_36">Foreign Relations, 1894, pages 36</ref> to
                                <ref target="frus1894#pg_47">47</ref>, which may be of service to
                            you.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
